<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="543" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1805,2010]" pageId="14" pageNumber="543">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1913,1938]" pageId="14" pageNumber="543">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Interstriae 
<number box="[452,480,1914,1938]" pageId="14" pageNumber="543" value="10.0">10</number>
sharply elevated far beyond level of metacoxae, protibiae without additional mesal tooth. Affiliated with species in the 
<taxonomicName box="[600,679,1950,1973]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Scolytodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="543" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis box="[600,679,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="543">atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the widely separated procoxae and broad protibiae. Distinguished from all species of that group by the closed ring of long erect golden setae in the female frons.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
