<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="545" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,836,861]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">Etymology.</emphasis>
From Latin 
<taxonomicName box="[484,574,836,860]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Scolytodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solarius">
<emphasis box="[484,574,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">solarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning ‘relating to the sun’, with reference to the circle-shaped ring of golden setae in the female frons.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1380,908,933]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,151,933]" box="[199,1380,908,933]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,497,908,933]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">Biology and distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[753,801,909,933]" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">type</typeStatus>
locality. It was collected from a 
<taxonomicName box="[1167,1270,908,931]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Urticaceae" genus="Cecropia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="16" pageNumber="545" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1167,1270,908,931]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="545">Cecropia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
leafstalk.
</paragraph>
